    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-15T15:55:23+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-15T15:55:23+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-15T06:25:23Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-15T06:25:23Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over NSW will allow a cold front to move across the far southeast of SA on Thursday. A second high pressure system is expected to move south of the Bight during Friday and Saturday ahead of another trough expected to brush the west and south on the weekend.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW005" description="Lower South East" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-15T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-15T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely from the late morning. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning and afternoon. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning west to southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:40am to 2:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 5 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the morning. Winds southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h tending southerly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Patches of frost in the morning, mainly in the north. Light winds becoming northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 2 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning. Winds north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending north to northwesterly during the day then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
